        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:26PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 425 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Dryden, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dryden and Terrell County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
